wikipedia_page.main: Mick Gannon (born 2 February 1943) is an English former professional footballer who played as a defender for Everton, Scunthorpe United, Crewe Alexandra, and Altrincham.

response: Mick Gannon (born 2 February 1947 in Dublin) was an Irish football player in the 1970s who played for Shelbourne and for Shamrock Rovers.
